  "prompt": "How do you plan your vacation in London?",
  "response": "Planning a vacation in London involves several key steps:\n\n1. Timing\n- Check weather conditions\n- Consider peak/off-peak tourist seasons\n- Look at events and festivals happening during your visit\n\n2. Budget\n- Determine your overall budget\n- Research accommodation costs\n- Plan for transportation expenses\n- Set aside money for attractions and dining\n\n3. Accommodation\n- Choose neighborhood based on interests\n- Consider hotels, hostels, Airbnb options\n- Book in advance for better rates\n\n4. Transportation\n- Get an Oyster Card for public transit\n- Consider London Underground (Tube)\n- Check travel passes\n- Plan for airport transfers\n\n5. Attractions\n- Research top attractions (Big Ben, Tower of London, British Museum)\n- Buy tickets in advance\n- Consider London Pass for multiple attractions\n- Check opening hours and prices\n\n6. Itinerary\n- Create a rough daily schedule\n- Group attractions by location\n- Allow flexibility\n- Include walking tours\n- Plan for rest and dining\n\n7. Practical Preparations\n- Check visa requirements\n- Get travel insurance\n- Exchange currency\n- Pack appropriate clothing\n- Bring adapters for electronics\n\n8. Additional Tips\n- Download useful apps\n- Learn basic local customs\n- Have emergency contact information",
